[SN]TITLE[SN]
The training school for Japan's mascots

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Mascots are big business in Japan but becoming one takes a lot of training at one of the country's specialist schools.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
29 September 2015 Last updated at 12:02 BST
The cute characters are very popular with children and they are used to promote national parks, trains, TV stations and well known landmarks, like the Tokyo Tower.
There is a special school in Tokyo where people can learn how to move and dance for huge audiences.
And Newsround reporter Leah went behind the scenes to find out what it takes.
